Reconciler Unit Tests Implementation

WHY: The reconciler (internal/state/reconcile.go) had 0% test coverage. This is a critical component that syncs local state with AWS resources - detecting orphaned AWS resources and stale local entries.

WHAT CHANGED:
1. Added ReconcileEC2API, ReconcileECSAPI, ReconcileELBV2API interfaces to enable mock testing
2. Added NewReconcilerWithClients() constructor for dependency injection
3. Refactored pagination from SDK paginators to manual token-based pagination
   - Reason: SDK paginators are tied to concrete client types, can't mock
   - Behavior unchanged: still handles large accounts with >1000 resources
4. Added 17 comprehensive test cases covering all reconciler functionality

DESIGN DECISIONS:
- Mock-based unit tests preferred over LocalStack integration tests
  - Faster execution (ms vs seconds)
  - No external dependencies
  - Same coverage for business logic
  - LocalStack can be added later if needed for e2e testing

COVERAGE IMPACT:
- internal/state package: 44.4% → 82.0%
- reconcile.go functions now have mock-based test coverage

